cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on improving the spatio-temporal representation learning for video recognition using a novel neural network architecture. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a kernelized classifier, which involves mathematical optimization (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the paper proposes a new framework for representation learning, which involves modeling diffusions between local and global features, indicating the use of neural networks (cs.NE).
